Role of Decision Making Body:
The Board of Directors oversees the management of the Company and its business. This includes selecting the Senior Management Team that is responsible for operating the Company's business, and monitors the performance of senior management. 

The Board’s core responsibilities include:
o Assessment of the performance of the Chief Executive Officer (“CEO”) and other senior management and setting their compensation;
o Succession planning for the CEO and senior management;
o Review of the Company’s strategies, implementation and results;
o Oversight of the integrity of the Company’s financial statements and the Company’s financial reporting process;
o Oversight of the Company’s processes for assessing and managing risk;
o Oversight of legal and regulatory compliance;
o Succession planning for the Board and key leadership roles on the Board and its committees;
o Nomination of candidates for director and appointment of committee members; and
o Provision of advice and counsel to management regarding significant issues facing the Company and review and approval of significant corporate actions.
